HEADWORD: Sporozoite
<hw>Spo`ro*zo"ite</hw> <pr>(sp⟦omac⟧`r⟦osl⟧*z⟦omac⟧"⟦imac⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>In certain Sporozoa, a small
active, usually elongate, sickle-shaped or somewhat amoeboid spore, esp.
one of those produced by division of the passive spores into which the
zygote divides. The sporozoites reproduce asexually.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sporran</ent>⟦br⟧
